goodness gracious last nite was pretty damn fun.  so heres the scenario, we're on our way to the tantric and 3 doors down show.  excitment is ripping through the car.  we go to the mcdonalds drive thru.  my dad makes small talk to the lady about the snow, i comment that shes probaly not used to snow in mexico.  we get on the road and zip down to constitution hall in DC.  grant and i get out of the car with colucch where we make our way to tantrics bus.  at the moment there was only the drum tech and the guitar tech on the bus, but we hung out with them for a while and watched a little bit of bruce allmighty. while we were watching grant and i got a couple of sweet vip passes.  after that we went down to the dressing room,and hung out with the band before they went onstage.  i enjoyed a coca cola, and grant had himself a yoohoo.  hugo the lead singer was drinking tea and singing to warm up his voice.  todd the guitarist was working out on the bowflex.  matt the drummer was walking around aimlessly.  jesse the bassist wasnt in the room.  we left, and went to go see brian, his sister, james, and eric we hung out with them untill the show started.  we went down to our seats and proceeded to get the fuck rocked out of us by tantric.  the only down note was there were these three stupid fat black chicks in front of us.  they were heckling and shit, but hugo got them to shut the fuck up.  my thoughts were hey at the end of the day, they're still fat and black.  so after the show we are all hanging out in the area next to the tshirt stand, when who else but hugo ferreria the lead singer of tantric comes out to shoot the shit with us.  we just hung out and talked with him and watched him drink and sign autographs and talk with his many many fans.  he was so dam cool, i mean how many rock stars just hang out with fans.  we also hung out with kevin the tour guitarist who is a really really great guy.  so we went back down to the dressing room, where it was now only hugo and kevin, but the guys from the opening band shinedown came in and hung out with us.  those are some pretty dam cool guys.  so we said goodbye to everyone after a while and went to see like 2 minutes of 3 doors down's show.  then we went out into the snowy snowy night, and i bought a 3 doors down shirt from a black guy for 10 bucks.  then we cruised all the way home with happy memories in our heads.  

rock on bitches
